# Workout SPA Editor Environment Variables

# Base path for deployment (e.g., GitHub Pages)
# VITE_BASE_PATH=/workout-spa-editor

# NOTE: The Umami website id is NOT a build-time env var. It is injected at
# deploy time as a runtime config substitution into `index.html` (see
# docs/analytics.md → "Runtime config injection"). Local dev intentionally
# has no analytics; the noop adapter wins.

# Bridge extensions (Garmin, Train2Go) are discovered at runtime via
# content script announcements. No extension IDs are required at build
# time; install the extension and the SPA will pick it up automatically.

# Cross-device sync: Google Cloud OAuth Client ID (PUBLIC — not a secret).
# A working default is committed in `.env`. Scope used is
# https://www.googleapis.com/auth/drive.appdata (non-sensitive). See
# docs/google-drive-sync.md for the Google Cloud setup and verification
# caveat. Override only when deploying under a different OAuth project.
# VITE_GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com
